                <h1>Best Primer for Covering Wallpaper: Top Picks</h1>
                <p>To effectively cover wallpaper, the best primer options are those that have strong adhesion and stain-blocking properties. Look for high-quality, oil-based or shellac primers, as they can seal old patterns and prevent bleed-through. Water-based alternatives are suitable for lighter wallpapers. Always test in a small area first!</p>
